                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.01/10–1949: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Strong</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Chungking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-10-19T05:00:00+07:00"
                            >October 19, 1949—5 a. m. [<hi rend="italic">p. m.?</hi>]</date>
                        <lb/> [Received October 19—7:03 a. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Cantel 1214. Chu Chang-wei confirms that Kunming selected as alternate capital by
                    Executive Yuan. Says no steps yet being taken make preparations there and
                    government will stay Chungking long as possible. Yunnan, according to Chu, will
                    be site of last-ditch stand. Says government feels will lose Szechuan but can
                    hold out long time in Yunnan.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Strong</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
